&lt;p&gt;Facilities Assistant (cleaner)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Two posts of 15 hours per week, Monday to Friday 4pm-7pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated and hard-working individuals to join our Facilities and Housekeeping team at Sussex Rehabilitation Centre at Brighton General Hospital, who will ensure our standards meet the National Specifications for Cleanliness in the NHS. The roles involve cleaning the hospital&#39;s clinical and non-clinical areas and securing the hospital at night, and as such include a considerable amount of manual handling and physical work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous cleaning experience would be an advantage, but not essential as training will be provided. Please give FULL details of any relevant experience on your application form to assist us with the shortlisting process. Any fields left blank or incomplete will not be able to be scored.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply online via the NHS Jobs website. If you are unable to use a computer to apply online, please contact the RECRUITMENT DEPARTMENT on 01273 696011 extension 5008 (quoting the job reference number) and request to be sent a paper copy application form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePauline HynesJob titleFacilities ManagerEmail addresssc-tr.recruitment@nhs.netTelephone number01273 696011 ext. 1134Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Simpson-Wells (01273 696 011 x 1236)&lt;/p&gt;
